@startuml
!pragma layout smetana

title Gromozeka: Who Does What?

left to right direction

skinparam backgroundColor #FCFCFA
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 14
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #475569
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam actorStyle awesome

actor "User" as User

rectangle "Gromozeka Server\n<size:12>Control center</size>\n\nReceives requests\nKeeps conversations and state\nAssigns work\nReturns progress and results" as Server #DCEBFF

node "Computer or virtual machine" as Host #F4F4F0 {
    rectangle "Gromozeka Worker\n<size:12>Trusted executor</size>\n\nReceives assigned work\nCalls an AI model when needed\nRuns available tools" as Worker #FFE9B8
    folder "Resources available on this machine\n\nFiles\nShell commands\nApplications and services" as Resources #DCF4DF

    Worker --> Resources : uses
}

User --> Server : asks for work
Server --> User : shows status and results
Server --> Worker : sends work to perform
Worker --> Server : returns progress and results

note bottom of Server
The Server coordinates work.
It does not execute the machine's tools itself.
end note

note bottom of Worker
The Worker can do whatever its operating-system account can do.
Gromozeka does not give it extra access to the machine.
end note

legend bottom left
One Server can coordinate several Workers.
Each Worker runs on a particular computer or virtual machine.
endlegend

@enduml
